description.narrative: Community-based child protection, psychosocial, and reintegration services are available for vulnerable boys and girls, including survivors of all forms of violence, children with disabilities, children on the move and children associated with armed conflict in targeted municipalities., which contributes to Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas, Other Cross-Sectoral Programme Areas (Covid), Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 girls and boys are better protected from violence, abuse and exploitation

description.narrative: In 2020, UNICEF and its partners continued to strengthen the protective environment for children at the community level. UNICEF focused on reaching the most vulnerable girls and boys (including conflict affected children, IDPs, migrants and refugees) with child protection services, including psychosocial and reintegration services, gender-based violence services and other specialized child protection services. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:16/08/2020
